 The products and services offered within Ireland’s cyber security firms were then identified from website

descriptions. The final descriptions were used to group firms into six broad service categories, using a 
 ‘best-fit’ methodology reflecting the main product and service offerings.

This taxonomy used in this study is informed by previous definitions designed in collaboration with the 
 Centre for Secure Information Technology (CSIT), which were developed to reflect the areas of relative 
 industrial strength on the island of Ireland. The definitions span 7 final categories and are outlined below:

Managed security service provision and advisory services;

Risk, compliance, and fraud;

Securing applications, networks, and cloud environments;

Operational technology, security, and connected devices;

Threat intelligence, monitoring, detection, and analysis;

Identification, authentication, and access control; and

